5 §4744.1. Labeling of non-lactational dairy protein products
6 A.(1) Any non-lactation dairy protein product offered for sale within this
7 state shall bear a clear and conspicuous disclosure statement that reads: "Produced
8 through microbial fermentation. Not derived from mammalian lactation."
9 (2) The disclosure shall also meet all of the following requirements:
10 (a) Appear on the principal display panel.
11 (b) Be in a font size not less than thirty-point type.
12 (c) Be in a typeface and color that contrast with the background.
13 (d) Be placed in close proximity to the product name.
14 Section 2. R.S. 3:4744(C) is hereby enacted to read as follows:
15 §4744. Applicability; prohibited activities
16 * * *
17 C.(1) No person, firm, or corporation shall manufacture for sale, sell, hold
18 or offer for sale, or distribute any non-lactational dairy protein product in this state.
19 (2) No non-lactational dairy protein product shall be labeled or marketed as
20 milk, cheese, yogurt, butter, ice cream, or any other dairy product intended for
21 human consumption.
22 (3) Any violation of this Section shall constitute a violation of this Part and
23 shall be subject to all enforcement authority, penalties, and remedies otherwise
24 provided by law.
25 Section 3. The provisions of Sections 1 and 4 and this Section of this Act shall
26 become effective upon signature by the governor or, if not signed by the governor, upon
27 expiration of the time for bills to become law without signature by the governor, as provided
28 by Article III, Section 18 of the Constitution of Louisiana. If vetoed by the governor and
29 subsequently approved by the legislature, this Act shall become effective on the day
30 following such approval.
